value.value: A portion of cortex (PO:0005708) that is part of a petiole (PO:0020038).
A phyllome vascular system (PO:0025206) that includes the totality of the portions of vascular tissue in their specific arrangement in a petal (PO:0025218).
An undeveloped shoot system (PO:0009006).
A bud that develops into a flower.
A bud that develops into an inflorescence.
A bud (PO:0000055) that develops into a vegetative shoot system (PO:0025607).

An initial cell (PO:0004011) that is part of a root apical meristem (PO:0020147) and by division gives rise to two cells, one of which remains in the meristem, while the other is produces different root cells.
A root initial cell (PO:0000059) that produces root cortex (PO:0000258) and root endodermis (PO:0005059). In direct contact with quiescent center (PO:0020149).

label.value: lateral root cap epidermal initial cell

value.value: A root initial cell (PO:0000059) that produces lateral root cap cells and root epidermis (PO:0006036).

An plant epidermal initial cell (PO:0000349) that undergoes several rounds of uneven division, each time giving rise to a larger daughter cell that differentiates into an epidermal ground cell and a smaller daughter cell that remains meristematic, until the meristematic cell (PO:0004010) differentiates into a guard mother cell (PO:0000351).
A procambial cell (PO:0025258) that is part of a leaf procambium (PO:0025259).

definition.value: Leaf procambial cells may be derived from the shoot apical meristem or can arise throughout the mesophyll of a developing leaf.

value.value: A pericycle cell that is adjacent to the protoxylem of a vascular bundle.

definition.value: Xylem pole pericycle cells are cells in the pericycle that are adjacent to the protoxylem pole of a vascular bundle. Pericycle cells that are adjacent to other xylem cells in the vascular bundle are not considered xylem pole pericycle cells. Xylem pole pericycle cells may retain some meristematic activity and are the site of lateral root initiation.

value.value: A pericycle cell that is adjacent to the protophloem of a vascular bundle.

definition.value: Phloem pole pericycle cells are cells in the pericycle that are adjacent to the protophloem pole of a vascular bundle. Pericycle cells that are adjacent to other phloem cells in the vascular bundle are not considered phloem pole pericycle cells. Phloem pole pericycle cells are distinct from xylem pole pericycle cells in that they display cytoplasmic characteristics of a more differentiated status.

value.value: A parenchyma cell of the mesophyll of a hydathode found between the xylem endings and the epidermis.

definition.value: Proposed to be involved in the retrieval of solutes from the xylem sap.

value.value: A root (PO:0009005) that forms one or more clusters of closely spaced lateral roots (PO:0020121) of limited growth along its length.

definition.value: The terms proteoid root, cluster root, and root cluster have all been used in the literature to describe either the proteoid root axis or clusters of rootlets, and caution should be taken when comparing studies because the definitions of these terms vary (Watts and Evans, 1999; Plant Physiology).

value.value: A parenchyma cell (PO:0000074) that is adjacent to a sieve tube element (PO:0000289) and arises from the same phloem mother cell (PO:0000400) as the sieve tube element.

definition.value: Companion cells are connected to sieve tube elements through plasmodesmata and function in phloem loading of small molecules, including photosynthate (either sucrose or raffinose-family oligosaccharides). May participate in phloem sucrose loading (GO:0009915). Molecules can be loaded into the companion cells from surrounding cells through either symplastic (via plasmodesmata) or apoplastic (transmembrane) transport. Unlike sieve tube elements, companion cells retain their nuclei and other organelles at maturity. A sieve tube element may have one or more or no companion cells associated with it. This term should not be used for other types of parenchyma cells (PO:0000074) that do not arise from the same phloem mother cell as a sieve tube element. Companion cells are found in angiosperms, as compared to albuminous cells (PO:0025412), which are found in non-angiosperm vascular plants. Companion cells may be specialized as transfer companion cells (PO:0025458), ordinary companion cells (PO:0025459), or intermediary companion cells (PO:0025460). Multiple types of companion cells may be found in the same plant.

value.value: A relatively unspecialized ground tissue cell with a nucleate protoplast.
An elongated plant cell with unevenly thickened non-lignified primary walls that is alive at maturity.
A parenchyma cell containing chloroplasts; a component of leaf mesophyll and other green parenchyma tissue.
A ground tissue cell (PO:0025030) with a lignified secondary cell wall.

definition.value: May be dead at maturity. The secondary cell wall of a sclerenchyma cell is often thicker than other cell types in the same plant structure, but it is not always easy to distinguish from tracheary elements (PO:0000290) or sclerified parenchyma cells (PO:0000074). Compare with collenchyma cells (PO:0000075) that are always alive at maturity, have irregularly thickened primary cell walls, and do not have lignified secondary cell walls. Collenchyma cells provides flexibility while sclerenchyma cells provide hardness. Sclerenchyma cells include plant fiber cells (PO:0025407) and sclerid cells (PO:0025418).

value.value: A cell with wall ingrowths (or invaginations) that increase the surface of the plasmalemma.

definition.value: Appear to be specialized for short-distance transfer of solutes. Transfer cells can occur anywhere there is a junction between two individuals, such as between a sporophyte and a gametophyte, or between a parasitic plant and its host.

value.value: An elongated cambial initial cell (PO:0000295) with approximately wedge-shaped ends that is part of the vascular cambium (PO:0005598) and gives rise to axial cells.
A cambial initial cell (PO:0000295) that gives rise to ray cells of the secondary xylem (PO:0005848) and secondary phloem (PO:0005043).
A gamete (PO:0025006) produced by an antheridium (PO:0025125) or a microgametophyte (PO:0025280).

definition.value: The sperm cell is usually smaller than the egg cell. Male gametes may be defined as the motile gamete, rather than the smaller gamete. Plant sperm cells lack a cell wall.

value.value: A portion of shoot system epidermis (PO:0006035) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029).

definition.value: Can occur on a stem or branch.

value.value: A shoot epidermal cell (PO:0025165) that surrounds a trichome (PO:0000282) and provides its support.

A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that has as part a separation layer (PO:0006211) and a protective layer (PO:0006212), and is involved in the abscission (GO:0009838) of a fruit (PO:0009001), flower (PO:0009046), leaf (PO:0025034) or other plant structure (PO:0009011).
Cell, usually two in number, in the micropylar end of the embryo sac of angiosperms associated with the egg in the egg apparatus.
A portion of endosperm (PO:0009089) tissue in which at least the first karyokinesis is not followed by cytokinesis.
A portion of endosperm (PO:0009089) in which the first karyokinesis event is accompanied by cytokinesis.
A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the region of the endosperm closest to the micropyle of the seed.
A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the part of the endosperm (PO:0009089) nearest the chalazal region of the plant ovule (PO:0020003) and forming a cyst-like structure.

definition.value: Not in current literature. More like an attribute.

value.value: A portion of shoot system epidermis (PO:0006035) that is part of a nectary (PO:0009035) .
A portion of cortex (PO:0005708) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029).

definition.value: Can occur in a stem or branch.

value.value: An area of densely packed cells in the shoot apex that divide infrequently.

definition.value: Functions as a population of stem cells that replenishes the meristem.

value.value: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) which is the organogenic region of the meristem, characterized by higher rates of cell division.
The region of the shoot apical meristem that lies below the central zone and is flanked by the peripheral zone.
A portion of reproductive shoot apical meristem tissue (PO:0008028) that gives rise to the floral organs (PO:0025395).

definition.value: In Zea mays and other grasses, the floret meristem is part of a spikelet and develops into a specific type of floret. If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the spikelet type that the meristem is part of. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet (PO:0009051), ear spikelet (PO:0006320), ear pedicellate spikelet (PO:0006348), ear sessile spikelet (PO:0006349), tassel spikelet (PO:0006309), tassel pedicellate spikelet (PO:0006312), tassel sessile spikelet (PO:0006311).

value.value: A meristem that gives rise to an inflorescence.
A shoot system meristem (PO:0006079) formed in an axil (PO:0025224).
A megaspore(s) that forms an embryo sac.

definition.value: If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret (PO:0009082), ear floret (PO:0006354), upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (PO:0006350), upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear (PO:0006352).

value.value: In monosporic and bisporic megasporogenesis: the megaspore(s) that would not participate in megagametogenesis.

definition.value: If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret (PO:0009082), ear floret (PO:0006354), upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (PO:0006350), upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear (PO:0006352).

value.value: A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) that is the inner most layer of a cortex (PO:0005708) and has a casparian strip in its anticlinal cell walls.

definition.value: Forms a sheath around the vascular system. It may have secondary walls later, part_of cortex.

value.value: A root epidermal cell (PO:0025164) that develops from a trichoblast (PO:0000262) and has as part a root hair (GO:0035618).

definition.value: Compare with non-hair root epidermal cell (PO:0000263). This term is for an entire epidermal cell that contains a root hair extension. To describe only the cell extension, see root hair (GO:0035618) or root hair tip (GO:0035619).

value.value: A portion of cortex (PO:0005708) that is part of a root (PO:0009005).

definition.value: In dicots and gymnosperms, the cortex consists of mainly parenchyma cells. In monocots sclerenchyma develops in addition to parenchyma.

value.value: A root epidermal cell (PO:0025164) that is the smaller cell produced by the asymmetric division of an epidermal intial cell (PO:0000349) and gives rise to a root hair (GO:0035618).
A root epidermal cell (PO:0025164) that develops from an epidermal initial (PO:0000349) and does not have as part a root hair (GO:0035618).

definition.value: Compare to root hair cell (PO:0000256), which develops from a trichoblast (PO:0000262).

value.value: A portion of primary xylem (PO:0000272) tissue that has as part one or more protoxylem tracheary elements (PO:0025575) embedded in parenchyma (PO:0005421) tissue.

definition.value: Develops while the vascular tissue (PO:0009015) is still elongating. When protoxylem tracheary elements (PO:0025575) are destroyed they may become obliterated by surrounding parenchyma cells (PO:0000074). Protoxylem has smaller elements than the metaxylem (PO:0000372).

value.value: A fiber cell (PO:0025407) that is part of a portion of xylem (PO:0005352) tissue.

definition.value: It may be difficult to distinguish xylem fiber cells, especially fiber tracheids (PO:0000355), from tracheary elements (PO:0000290). Fiber tracheids have bordered pits with smaller pit cavities than the vessel members (PO:0002003) or tracheids (PO:0000301) of the same wood and a distinct pit cavity leading to the cell lumen through the cell wall.

value.value: A unicellular or multicellular plant structure (PO:0009011) that forms a non-sclerified outgrowth from the epidermis (PO:0005679).

definition.value: This class is the union of unicellular trichome (PO:0025537) and multicellular trichome (PO:0025162). A trichome can vary in length and shape and may be branched or unbranched.  It may be glandular or non-secretory.
